=head1 DESCRIPTION

The name and values of a manual Amazon RDS DB snapshot attribute.
Manual DB snapshot attributes are used to authorize other Amazon Web
Services accounts to restore a manual DB snapshot.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 AccountIds => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

The Amazon Web Services account IDs that have access to the manual
Amazon RDS DB snapshot. If the value C<all> is specified, then the
Amazon RDS DB snapshot is public and can be copied or restored by all
Amazon Web Services accounts.

=over

=item *

If the configuration is for an existing Amazon RDS DB snapshot and you
do not specify the C<accountIds> in C<RdsDbSnapshotAttributeValue>,
then the access preview uses the existing shared C<accountIds> for the
snapshot.

=item *

If the access preview is for a new resource and you do not specify the
specify the C<accountIds> in C<RdsDbSnapshotAttributeValue>, then the
access preview considers the snapshot without any attributes.

=item *

To propose deletion of an existing shared C<accountIds>, you can
specify an empty list for C<accountIds> in the
C<RdsDbSnapshotAttributeValue>.

=back




